'''Ibrahim Mbaye''' (born 24 January 2008) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

== Club career ==
Mbaye started his youth career in 2013 at ES Guyancourt before joining [[FC Versailles 78|Versailles]] in 2015.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=Barroso |first=José |date=7 August 2024 |title=Qui est Ibrahim Mbaye, le jeune attaquant de 16 ans buteur en amical avec le PSG ? |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Qui-est-ibrahim-mbaye-le-jeune-attaquant-de-16-ans-buteur-en-amical-avec-le-psg/1489642 |access-date=14 August 2024 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr}}</ref> In 2018, at the age of 10, he joined the [[Paris Saint-Germain Academy]].<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":2">{{FFF player|id=10898-mbaye-ibrahim}}</ref> In the 2023–24 season, while aged 16, Mbaye helped the PSG under-19s achieve victory in the [[Championnat National U19]] play-offs, scoring against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in a 2–0 win in the semi-finals and setting up [[Senny Mayulu]]'s second goal in the 3–1 victory over [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] in the final.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Foot : Senny Mayulu et les U19 du PSG vainqueurs d'Auxerre en finale du Championnat national |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Senny-mayulu-et-les-u19-du-psg-vainqueurs-d-auxerre-en-finale-du-championnat-national/1475182 |access-date=2024-09-03 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

On 14 July 2024, Mbaye was called up for pre-season with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]'s first team, having impressed head coach [[Luis Enrique]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mechenoua |first=Marc |date=2024-07-14 |title=Tests médicaux, programme, joueurs sur le départ… tout ce qu'il faut savoir sur la rentrée du PSG |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/tests-medicaux-programme-joueurs-sur-le-depart-tout-ce-quil-faut-savoir-sur-la-rentree-du-psg-14-07-2024-IPHK22B73ZB5RAV5TUTDEXYHEY.php |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 July 2024 |title=Ibrahim Mbaye, le nouveau chouchou de Luis Enrique |url=https://lemeilleurdupsg.com/article/ibrahim-mbaye-le-nouveau-chouchou-de-luis-enrique |access-date=14 August 2024 |website=Le Meilleur du PSG |language=Fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2024-07-14 |title=PSG : Luis Enrique convoque Mbaye pour la reprise |url=https://www.paristeam.fr/actu-psg/actualite/psg-luis-enrique-convoque-mbaye-pour-la-reprise-68404 |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=Paristeam |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 7 August, he made his first appearance and start for the club in a 2–2 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] draw against [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]].<ref name=":3" /> Nine minutes into the match, he scored PSG's first goal of the season after receiving an assist from [[Marco Asensio]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Amical : Le premier but de la saison du PSG pour Ibrahim Mbaye ! |url=https://www.beinsports.com/fr-fr/football/friendlies/articles-video/amical-le-premier-but-de-la-saison-du-psg-pour-ibrahim-mbaye-2024-08-07 |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=fr-fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Ibrahim Mbaye: At 16 Years Old, Scores His First Goal with PSG Thanks to an Assist from Marco Asensio |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/articles-video/ibrahim-mbaye-at-16-years-old-scores-his-first-goal-with-psg-thanks-to-an-assist-from-marco-asensio-2024-08-07 |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-08 |title=PSG : bientôt un premier contrat pro pour la pépite Ibrahim Mbaye ? |url=https://www.sport.fr/football/psg-bientot-un-premier-contrat-pro-pour-la-pepite-ibrahim-mbaye-1200882.shtm |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=Sport.fr |language=fr-fr}}</ref> Following PSG's second pre-season match on 10 August against [[RB Leipzig]], in which Mbaye was a starter, Luis Enrique praised Mbaye's performance, saying he was satisfied with his play.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2024-08-12 |title=PSG : Luis Enrique a félicité Ibrahim Mbaye |url=https://www.paristeam.fr/actu-psg/actualite/psg-luis-enrique-a-felicite-ibrahim-mbaye-68628 |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=Paristeam |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Brilleau |first=Olivier |title=PSG : Quand Mbaye tape dans l'oeil de Luis Enrique |url=https://www.planetepsg.com/news-109231-club-quand_mbaye_tape_dans_loeil_de_luis_enrique.html |access-date=2024-08-14 |website=PlanetePSG.com |language=fr}}</ref>

On 16 August, Mbaye made his official debut for PSG, playing the first half of a 4–1 victory away to [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]], the first match of the [[2024–25 Ligue 1]] season. He became the youngest player to start a game for PSG at 16 years, 6 months, and 23 days, surpassing the record of his teammate [[Warren Zaïre-Emery]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=Une première et déjà un record pour Ibrahim Mbaye |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/une-premiere-et-un-deja-un-record-pour-ibrahim-mbaye-le-havre-ac-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-20242025 |access-date=16 August 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]] |language=fr}}</ref> On 7 February 2025, it was announced that Mbaye had signed his first professional contract with PSG, a deal until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tournoux |first=Manu |date=7 February 2025 |title=PSG announces the signing of a new contract for three young people |url=https://frenchfootballweekly.com/2025/02/07/psg-announces-the-signing-of-a-new-contract-for-three-young-people/ |access-date=7 February 2025 |website=French Football Weekly}}</ref> On 26 February, he made his debut in [[2024–25 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]] by coming on as a substitute against fourth-tier side [[Stade Briochin]], as PSG won the game 7–0 and qualified for the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Saint-Brieuc 0-7 PSG |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/coupe-de-france/2024-2025/saint-brieuc-psg-live/670856 |website=L’Equipe |access-date=26 February 2025}}</ref> On 29 March 2025, he scored his first professional goal with PSG, in a 6–1 [[2024–25 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] win against [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ASSE 1-6 PSG, Ligue 1 |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2024-2025/asse-psg-live/656097 |website=PSG |access-date=29 March 2025}}</ref>

On 15 June 2025, Mbaye was subbed on in a 4–0 win against [[Atlético Madrid]] in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup Group B|2025 FIFA Club World Cup]]; at the age of 17 years, 4 months and 22 days old, he became the youngest Frenchman (and the sixth youngest player overall) to play in the [[FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Group B - Match 3 PSG ATM |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/match-centre/match/10005/289175/289176/400019155 |website=FIFA |access-date=15 June 2025}}</ref> On 13 August 2025, Mbaye came on as a substitute in the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup]] as PSG beat [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], overtaking [[Ryan Giggs]] as the youngest player to win the [[UEFA Super Cup]] at the age of 17 years, 6 months and 19 days. He also became the youngest Frenchman to play in the Super Cup, and the second-youngest player ever after [[Ronald de Boer]] in [[1987 European Super Cup|1987]] to play in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |title=Paris vs Tottenham |url=https://fr.uefa.com/uefasupercup/match/2045107--paris-vs-tottenham/ |website=UEFA |access-date=13 August 2025}}</ref>

Mbaye made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut as a substitute in a 4–0 win over [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] on 17 September 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/757661/atalanta-paris-saint-germain |title=Paris Saint-Germain 4–0 Atalanta |publisher=ESPN |date=17 September 2025 }}</ref> On 13 May 2026, he netted a stoppage-time goal in a 2–0 away win over [[RC Lens|Lens]], securing his club's [[2025–26 Ligue 1|14th Ligue 1]] title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.com/articles/soccer/paris-saintgermain-clinches-league-title-with-20-win-over-closest-rival-lens |title=Paris Saint-Germain clinches league title with 2-0 win over closest rival Lens |publisher=FOX SPORTS |date=13 May 2026 }}</ref>

== International career ==
Mbaye has represented France at various youth levels.<ref name=":2" /> At the 2024 [[Montaigu Tournament]], he helped the [[France national under-16 football team|France under-16s]] achieve victory while picking up the award for the competition's best player.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2024-08-08 |title=PSG : duel Maroc-Sénégal pour Ibrahim Mbaye ! |url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/psg-ibrahim-mbaye-origine-maroc-senegal-parents |access-date=2024-08-13 |website=www.afrik-foot.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref> He was part of the [[France national under-18 football team|France under-18s]] that finished third in the 2024 [[Lafarge Foot Avenir]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Un troisième nul pour conclure à Limoges |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/13151-un-troisieme-nul-pour-conclure-a-limoges.html |access-date=2024-09-10 |website=www.fff.fr}}</ref>

In November 2025, Mbaye received his first call-up to the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Matchs Amicaux Brésil vs Sénégal et Sénégal vs Kenya: Le Coach Pape Thiaw Publie sa Liste|url=https://fsfoot.sn/matchs-amicaux-bresil-vs-senegal-et-senegal-vs-kenya-le-coach-pape-thiaw-publie-sa-liste/|date=6 November 2025|access-date=10 November 2025|language=fr}}</ref> making his debut against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] on 15 November.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.psg.fr/en/content/marquinhos-and-brazil-triumph-over-mbayes-senegal-psg-friendlies-national-teams-2025-2026 |title=Marquinhos and Brazil triumph over Mbaye's Senegal |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |date=15 November 2025 }}</ref> Three days later, on 18 November, on his second cap, he scored his first international goal in an 8–0 victory in a friendly game against [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]], becoming at 17 years 9 months and 25 days Senegal’s youngest ever goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |title=Un but, des passes et un record pour Mbaye avec le Sénégal |url=https://allezparis.fr/club/un-but-des-passes-et-un-record-pour-mbaye-avec-le-senegal-50931 |website=Allez Paris |access-date=18 November 2025}}</ref> On 15 December 2025, Mbaye's request to switch international allegiance to Senegal was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-CAP">{{cite news |url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform |title=FIFA Change of Association Platform |website=knowledge.fifa.com |date=15 December 2025|access-date=15 December 2025}}</ref>

On 23 December 2025, he played Senegal’s first [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations Group D|group stage]] game at the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]] against [[Botswana national football team|Botswana]], which is held in his maternal ancestral Morocco, to become at 17 years 10 months and 29 days the youngest Senegalese ever to play at the [[Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Stats Foot |url=https://x.com/Statsdufoot/status/2003504086839414865 |website=X |access-date=23 December 2025}}</ref>

On 3 January 2026, he scored his second goal with Senegal in a 3–1 win over [[Sudan national football team|Sudan]] in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations knockout stage#Senegal vs Sudan|2025 Africa Cup of Nations round of 16]], to become, at 17 years 11 months and 10 days, his country's youngest ever goalscorer in the [[Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Stats Foot on X |url=https://x.com/Statsdufoot/status/2007517111552467213?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E2007517111552467213%7Ctwgr%5Eebdfd0b806ab6208e549f00031f9b467481ca710%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onzemondial.com%2Fcan%2Fpsg-mbaye-plus-jeune-buteur-de-la-can-depuis-2000-lexploit-incroyable-975889 |website=X |access-date=3 January 2026}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Born in France, Mbaye is of Moroccan descent through his mother and Senegalese descent through his father.<ref name=":0" />

